-- Damas Says It Expects to Sign Extension of Debt Standstill in Coming Weeks
-- Inal Ersan
-- 2010-07-18T05:07:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/damas-says-it-expects-to-sign-extension-of-debt-standstill-in-coming-weeks.html

          
          
             Damas International Ltd., a Dubai-
based jewelry retailer, said it expects to sign an extension of
the standstill accord with its lenders in the coming weeks.  
 “Damas has been in talks with banks to restructure its
debts and has been operating under a standstill agreement,”
according to a company statement to Nasdaq Dubai today. “The
extension would serve as an interim arrangement till the
restructuring is finalized.”  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Inal Ersan in Dubai at 
 iersan@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        